================
description
================

1) This program accept file name and offset from user, and removes all the data from that
offset.
3) Required filename and offset will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	file name, file offset
	output	:	result - status of execution
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p1="parameter_value1", p2="parameter_value2"
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1) If the given file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
	2) If file offset is 0, then it removes all data from file
	
